comments.body:
@adelton No, I already have PR #6981 open to fix the links in the Readme, hence why I suggest reverting the changes in the ReadMe and docs/installation/linux.md to get only the other changes in as part of this PR.
You then open another PR in the docs repo [here](https://github.com/PowerShell/PowerShell-Docs) to update the actual installation doc and once the doc PR is in, you can then add another PR here with the updated readme once the Doc change is live. Sorry, it is normally not that complicated/convoluted, you just had bad luck with the timing of other changes.
I think this makes sense from a process perspective though. Microsoft needs to first test that everything works well with Fedora 28 before announcing it.
